'''Carnatic''' usually refers to: *[[Carnatic region]], Southern India *[[Carnatic music]], the classical music of Southern India
'''Carnatic''' may also refer to: *[[Carnatic Wars]], a series of military conflicts in India during the 18th century *{{ship|HMIS|Carnatic|J199}}, a Bangor class minesweeper of the Royal Indian Navy, that served in World War II *{{ship|HMS|Carnatic|1783}}, a 74-gun third rate ship of the line of the Royal Navy, launched at Deptford in 1783 *{{ship|HMS|Carnatic|1823}}, a 74-gun third rate ship of the line of the Royal Navy, launched at Portsmouth Dockyard in 1823 *[[Carnatic (1787 EIC ship)|''Carnatic'' (1787 EIC ship)]], an East Indiaman that made six voyages for the British East India Company between 1788 and 1802 *[[SS Carnatic|SS ''Carnatic'']], a P&O steamer with an early compound engine
